      "content": "yeah i hear you, but the security audit is pretty strict about minimizing overhead. the goal is to move towards a more event-driven model where you aren't constantly polling or scanning things anyway. \n\ni'm actually looking at the IAM policy diff right now, and once this commit goes through, your role will be scoped down to basically just metadata access. if you think it's going to be a problem, maybe you can suggest a way to handle the scaling requirements using the other existing service accounts instead? that way you won't have to worry about your own permissions being so limited.",
